					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You don't need &quot;Overarguments&quot; if you lift &quot;Argumentpush&quot; out of the subroutine and put it somewhere else.<br /><br />The stack manipulation technique doesn't seem too bad (see below), but I like your method better. Maybe there's a better way though. What does CC65 do for arguments?<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">; Push the arguments<br />lda #1<br />pha<br />lda #2<br />pha<br />lda #3<br />pha<br />jsr subroutine<br />; Pop the arguments<br />txa<br />axs #5<br />txs<br />rts<br /><br />subroutine:<br />tsx<br />; Access the arguments without popping<br />lda $0100-3,x<br />lda $0100-4,x<br />lda $0100-5,x<br />rts<br /></div></div>

					
							<br /><br />
							<span class="gensmall">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7486">pubby</a> on Fri Apr 29, 2016 9:22 pm, edited 1 time in total.</span>
