				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Something I've considered, that's sort of a similar kind of optimization, is finding a way to minimize the size of argument preamble for repetitive function calls with immediate arguments. This is a size over speed optimization, though, and you really need a large number of arguments and high repetitive usage to make this worth doing. As such, I've yet to actually find it useful- every time I've considered it, it was not a desirable trade.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">.macro QUICK_BLOO a,b,c,d,e,f<br />jmp :+<br />.byte a,b,c,d,e,f<br />:<br />jsr bloo<br />.endmacro<br /><br />; ...<br /><br />bloo:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ; fetch return value from stack, find the arguments 6 bytes back (+2 for the jsr instruction minus increment)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; tsx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; lda $100+1, X<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sec<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sbc #&lt;(6+2)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sta ptr+1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; lda $100+2, X<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sbc #&gt;(6+2)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sta ptr+0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ; now we can access the inline arguments like:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ldy #3<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; lda (ptr), Y ; fetch argument 3<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ; ...<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; rts</div></div>

					
