					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">pubby wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">; Access the arguments without popping<br />lda $0100-3,x<br />lda $0100-4,x<br />lda $0100-5,x<br /></div></div><br />I'm pretty sure that's wrong - on the 6502, the stack grows <strong>downward</strong>.<br /><br />In other words, $0100,X points to where the <strong>next</strong> byte will be pushed, $0101,X and $0102,X are the return address, and $0103,X / $0104,X / $0105,X are the parameters you pushed.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><strong>LDA $100-N, X</strong> is going to be 5 (unfortunately always a page crossing)</div><br />Thus, the above mentioned page crossing is <em>never</em> a concern.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
